<br>
Does anyone else think the idea of turning the click combine tradeskill system into a similuated combat style encounter complete with abilities like &quot;cool metal&quot; is a tad cheesy. Let me rephrase that.  How about a freaking joke on all of us.<br>
<br>
Next lets go on to item wear and repair.  I understand the concept behind item wear but I fail to see exactly how the need to feed your local tradeskill gimp plat to perform a nonsensical service actually adds to my experience.<br>
<br>
Speaking of wear I can see so many ways this could be fubar, heres a short list.<br>
<br>
Certain items shouldn't decay AT ALL, I've seen no mention of exemptions.<br>
<br>
It's presumed that people will grow out of items mostly before they wear out.  What situations in eq1 would this not be true hmmm.<br>
<br>
Situations where items that have some sentimental value (for some anyway somewhat cheesy I know)<br>
<br>
Situations where items that are essentially good for a large range of levels especially when upgrade options are lacking.<br>
<br>
Situations where items which take an extreme time commitment.<br>
<br>
The fact that some people reach a point in the game and don't progress towards uberity and are thus stuck with certain things for a long period of time. <br>
<br>
Situations in which people aren't that concerned about gear and keep similar gear for long periods.<br>
<br>
Situations where people choose to hang out and have fun in eq and not pursue gear upgrades.<br>
<br>
In all of the above have fun recamping gear that decides to poof.<br>
<br>
Lets move on to the single most idiodic portion, the death system.  This just takes the cake.  I guess what happens when you die is that when you croak you have 2 choices.  Hover at your corpse until rezed with no ability to play at all ever again until a rezer is found or destroy a randomly chosen possession for the privlige of playing at all.<br>
<br>
Bet you thought rez dependance was bad in eq1 well you obviously haven't seen anything yet.  Nobody will go anywhere or do anything without a rezer present.  <br>
<br>
Soloing is pretty much out especially in out of the way places.  Ditto with exploration.  I don't know how the hell this would work with pvp and I guess if your rezer dies he'll be all but forced to sac an item and more likely than not do it frequenty in order to be able to get everyone else back in the action. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hibashira>Hibashira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 468<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 4:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26846.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The blatent stupidity of certain aspects of EQ2</span><hr size=1> Hmmm, contrary to what you think, one of my first toon will be a craftsman (or whatever they call it) class.  I for one am glad that what you are not part of the EQ2 design team. /shrug <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328193"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hibashirasakai/HibashiraNewHalfSize.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=macfudd>Macfudd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 4:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26846.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>  The blatent stupidity of certain aspects of EQ2</span><hr size=1> I was about to post the 