<br>
I completely agree on the death system though.  I like if I die knowing that I have a 3 hour window to get a rez where I can run off and do other things.  If there is no Cleric/Paladin in the zone I can continue to solo until I see one.  It'd get a tad boring having to wait on a rezzer (and I'm betting this ability will be given to more than a couple classes) to come near you.  The problem they have though is they can't let people &quot;eat&quot; deaths or there would be minimal penalty to death.  The way I understand it, when you die you have an exp debt that you have to pay off.  However, it slowly reduces on its own over a period of time.  For example, if you die you get a debt of 100points.  5% of your gained exp will go to pay that off.  However, if you log off and come back 24 hours later your debt will be mostly gone.  <br>
<br>
Item Decay is one of those things that you are probably going to be seeing in more and more MMORPGs over the future.  EQ's economy and the mudflation in it is quite an example to other developers.  No item can ever retain it's original value.  Items removing themselves from the game ensures that there will never come a point where an item becomes near worthless.<br>
<br>
However, they haven't really said too much on how this system is going to work.  It might not be too bad overall. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
