ard.<br>
<br>
Here is the peoblem they are amking with EQ2.<br>
<br>
They are attempting to capture the casual player, but at the same time are trying to push the hardcore gamer away.<br>
Why do I believe this, lets look:<br>
<br>
1) Non Dropped Items. I can understand the need, but hardcore gamers *WANT* to show off the fact that they have the best gear, the most xp, the best skills, whatever.  &quot;I got this from Fennin Ro&quot; vs. &quot;I had a grand master tailor craft this from Fennin Ro's hair!&quot;  Tradeskill items == Questing. Questing == needless time sink.  Time sink == stupid waste of time.<br>
<br>
2) Item loss. Holy shit Batman, didn't they learn after Veeshan's Peak, or Plane of Fear, or even Plane of Hate?<br>
<br>
3) Anti-mudflation.  Basically this requires all gamers to take the same ammount of time to reach the max level.  Which means if you join the game, and 90% of the players are level 150, and it takes 2 years for a normal gamer to reach level 150, then you still have to work for 2 years.  After which the original players have been playing for 4 years, and likely can get to even higher level.<br>
<br>
4) The only way to Reward Tradeskillers is to allow their items to be better than many other items.<br>
<br>
5) They are appealing to the casual gamers. This is stupid.  EQ should be their hardcore genre, not the casual genre.  What is the purpose of EQ? To raid.  Sure, maybe 10% don't really raid, but why are those people playing the game? Because of their friends, who are more likely to play because they like to raid.<br>
<br>
6) Item wear.  One of my good friends was in an uber guild. He got lots of nice drops, and then burned out on the 'must raid 8 hours per day' mentality, and started a guild that was much lower. Thus he never needed upgrades, and had his items for far longer than their duration.  He is thus being penalized for NOT keeping the same pace, since his items will last for longer than their planned lifespan.<br>
<br>
7) Hyper realism.  Sony is attempting to make the game as &quot;Role-play&quot; as they can make it. Sorry, if I want to Role play in a 'realistic' world, I will bust out some character sheets and my dice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laerielarcanium>laeriel Arcanium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 258<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 5:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26846.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.directsecurity.com/MJ.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The blatent stupidity of certain aspects of EQ2</span><hr size=1> Your bitching about a game that isnt even beta yet?  If you think they are going to just leave in things that are detrimintal to the profitability, i would say you are in for a shock.<br>
