<br>
I used to play a game Meridian 59.  It was PvP.  When you died, anyone, could loot your corpse clean.  Often there would be a race to a dead corpse, some would loot and hold the items, try to find you and give you back what you lost.  Others, if nobody was around to notice, would just loot you and sell off your gear anonymously.<br>
<br>
Now, if this happend in EQ, people would be screaming.  Imagine dying while soloing in some remote area only to come back and find a naked corpse.<br>
<br>
However, it worked in Meridian because it did not take you long to gear up again.  Losing all your items hurt some but it was not the end of the world either.  More of ones strenght was based on their learned skills and abilities of the character.  <br>
<br>
There were some irreplaceable items in the game that were given out by the &quot;gods&quot; (GMs) for winning special events, these items were very uber.  You didn't see people wearing them out and about thought, they would be banked except for screenshots and special events where the risk of them being lost was nill (like an areana tornement)<br>
